Celtics Rally to Beat Knicks 87-85 in Opening Game of NBA Playoff Series

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-04-18T01:41:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/celtics-rally-to-beat-knicks-87-85-in-opening-game-of-nba-playoff-series.html
The Boston Celtics beat the New
York Knicks 87-85 in Game 1 of their National Basketball
Association first-round playoff series as  Ray Allen  hit a 3-
pointer with 11 seconds left.   Allen scored 24 points for the Celtics, who rallied from a
12-point halftime deficit at TD Garden in Boston.  Paul Pierce 
added 18 points for Boston, which will host Game 2 on April 19.  The Knicks, back in the NBA playoffs for the first time
since 2004, havenâ€™t won a postseason game since April 29, 2001.
Carmelo Anthony, who scored 15 points for New York, missed a 3-
